"That's tough, really tough. In five-set format I haven't done it yet," Bublik said. "But I'll try to use my chances."

The 28-year-old hit 22 aces against Paul and won 83 per cent of his first-serve points. He also used his drop shot to great effect against the American to keep him off balance throughout.



